Written evidence submitted by Resolution (LAI 004)defaultTransforming Legal AiddefaultThis evidence sets out some of the issues raised by the proposed 
defaultintroduction of a residence test for legal aid claimants in children and family cases.
defaultAbout Resolution defaultResolution, which was formerly known as the Solicitors Family Law Association (SFLA), is an organisation of 6,500 members who believe in a constructive
default, non‐confrontational approach to family law matters. Resolution also campaigns for improvements to the family justice system. 
